==Abstract==

This IIP specifies watchtower protocol for Lightning channel breach detection and response.

==Motivation==

Lightning requires monitoring for counterparty cheating. Watchtowers provide:
* 24/7 monitoring when node is offline
* Automated breach response
* Penalty transaction broadcast

==Specification==

===Watchtower Registration===

Client sends registration request:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Field !! Description
|-
| client_pubkey || Client's public key (2592 bytes)
|-
| reward_address || Address for watchtower payment
|-
| max_updates || Maximum state updates
|}

===State Updates===

For each commitment, client sends encrypted blob:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Field !! Description
|-
| locator || SHA3-256(txid)[0:16] (16 bytes)
|-
| encrypted_blob || ChaCha20 encrypted penalty tx
|}

The locator is derived from the commitment txid. When watchtower sees a matching transaction, it decrypts and broadcasts the penalty.

===Blob Encryption===

<pre>
key = SHA3-256(breach_txid)
encrypted = ChaCha20(key, penalty_tx || reward_output)
</pre>

===Breach Response===

When watchtower detects breach (matching locator):
# Decrypt penalty transaction
# Add reward output to penalty tx
# Broadcast penalty transaction
# Claim breach funds

===Watchtower Fees===

Fee models:
* Per-update fee: Small payment per state update
* Breach reward: Percentage of recovered funds
* Subscription: Flat periodic fee

==Security Considerations==

* Watchtower cannot steal funds (only penalty tx data)
* Multiple watchtowers recommended
* Encrypted blobs protect channel privacy

